      <p>Most people have two kidneys, each about 10 centimetres (4 inches) long. They are positioned in the back of the body behind the lower ribs.</p>
      <p>A healthy kidney is basically a filtering system. In fact, each kidney is made up of about a million filtering units called <a href="glossary.php#Nephrons">nephrons</a>.</p> 
