      <p>
        As blood passes through the kidneys, it is &quot;cleaned&quot; - the body's waste products and excess fluid are removed. These waste products, along with the excess fluid, are then sent through the <a href="glossary.php#Ureters">ureters</a> to the <a href="glossary.php#Bladder">bladder</a>. Then they are passed out of the body as <a href="glossary.php#Urine">urine</a>.
      </p> 
      <p>
        Healthy kidneys also balance the chemicals in the blood, and produce <a href="glossary.php#Hormone">hormones</a> which control <a href="glossary.php#Blood_pressure">blood pressure</a> and maintain healthy <a href="glossary.php#Blood_cells">blood cells</a> and bones.
      </p>
